Title: Series: Fasti di Napoleone
Description: Plate 15: Bonaparte's Egyptian campaign showing him leading his troops in preparation for battle; at centre a winged Victory arrives carrying a palm and crown of glory and at right is a river god representing the Nile Engraving
Curator's comments: For comment on series see 1872,0113.684.1 This is the second of five plates on the Egyptian campaign. See "Mito e storia nei 'Fasti di Napoleone' di Andrea Appiani", Rome, 1986, n.xv.
Associated names: Representation of: Napoléon I, Emperor of the French (Napoleon)
Associated events: Associated Event: Napoleon's campaign in Egypt 1798-1799
